<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0251 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author outlines just some of the reasons why business logic inexorablyleads to the conclusion that Congress should approve the sale of Conrailto Norfolk Southern. If the legislators who espouse the ideals so resoundinglyrejected in November of 1984 and those legislators who pin-re-electioncampaigns to the politics of this issue will stop and think about thisas a business transaction, the authors think they will agree with usthat Norfolf Southern is the right choice. The market is a powerful forceand the market has elected NS. The authors hope that the members of thisdistinguished audience will help debunk the politics of Conrail and supporttheir position.</TEXT></DOC>